<dl id="un1013c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013c"> (NLI.3) 13(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> our beloved H.P.B.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In some respects he <font color="green">[Shamsi Tabr&iuml;z, Jal&amacr;l&apos;s Teacher]</font> recalls <mark>our own loved H. P. B.</mark>, and like Socrates, he possessed violent passions, suffered dire poverty, and died a violent death. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), J. M. Watkins, &ldquo;Jal&amacr;lu&apos;dd&iuml;n Rumi&rdquo; 302</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07255h" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07255h">VI.C.07:255(h)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
